      "code": "const { BREP } = api;\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------\n// Project enclosure shell — 80 x 50 x 30 (mm), open top, BREP/replicad.\n// Base sits on the XY plane (z = 0). Centred in X/Y.\n//\n// IMPORTANT: BREP.box's Z range is [0, size[2]] (NOT centred). X and Y\n// ARE centred. So `BREP.box([80, 50, 30])` already sits with its base at\n// z=0 and top at z=30 — no translate needed for the outer shell.\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------\n\n// --- Outer shell (filleted FIRST, before any cuts) ---\nconst outerBox = BREP.box([80, 50, 30]);\n\n// Fillet the 4 vertical corner edges (3 mm) — edges parallel to Z.\nconst outerVertFilleted = outerBox.fillet(3, { inDirection: [0, 0, 1] });\n\n// Fillet the bottom outer perimeter (1 mm).\n// After vertical fillets the four bottom edges + four corner quarter-arcs\n// form one closed loop at z=0. parallelToPlane:'XY' alone would also grab\n// the top loop — exclude it with a nearPoint scoped to the lower half.\n// Bottom-edge midpoints: (±40, 0, 0), (0, ±25, 0)  → distance ≤ 40 from (0,0,0).\n// Top-edge midpoints: those points at z=30 → distance ≥ 30 from origin,\n//   actually exactly 30 for (0,0,30). So put the nearPoint at z=-5 to push\n//   the top edges out: bottom max ≈ sqrt(40²+5²)=40.3; top min ≈ sqrt(0+0+35²)=35\n//   — overlapping. Better: use nearPoint at (0,0,-100), withinDist=110.\n//   Distance from (0,0,-100) to bottom midpoint (40,0,0) = sqrt(1600+10000)=107.7.\n//   To top midpoint (0,0,30) = 130. So withinDist=110 includes bottom,\n//   excludes top. (Generous margin: 107.7 < 110 < 130.)\nconst outer = BREP.label(\n  outerVertFilleted.fillet(1, {\n    parallelToPlane: 'XY',\n    nearPoint: [0, 0, -100],\n    withinDist: 110,\n  }),\n  'shell',\n  { color: '#27ae60' },\n);\n\n// --- Inner cavity (74 x 44 x 27, walls = 3 mm, floor = 3 mm) ---\n// Cavity sits from z=3 to z=31 (overshoot by 1 mm so the cut clearly opens\n// the top — even after the lid lip step is removed).\nconst cavityBox = BREP.box([74, 44, 28]).translate([0, 0, 3]);\n// Round inner vertical corners (1.5 mm).\nconst cavity = cavityBox.fillet(1.5, { inDirection: [0, 0, 1] });\n\n// --- Lid lip step (75.5 x 45.5 x 1.6 at the very top) ---\n// Cut a shallow wider pocket the lid drops into.  Pocket footprint is\n// 75.5×45.5 (so it's wider than the cavity 74×44 by 0.75 mm on each side —\n// that's the lip the lid rests on). Goes from z=28.5 to z=30.1 (1.6 mm tall,\n// overshoots by 0.1 mm so the cut yields a clean step).\nconst lidLip = BREP.box([75.5, 45.5, 1.6]).translate([0, 0, 28.5]);\n\n// --- Vent slots (4 on the +Y long side wall) ---\n// Each slot: 2 mm wide (X) × 5 mm deep (Y, > 3 mm wall) × 12 mm tall (Z).\n// Vertical centre inside the cavity: z = (3 + 28.5)/2 ≈ 15.75, so the slot\n// box spans z = 9.75 .. 21.75.\n// Spread along X at -12, -4, 4, 12 (pitch 8 mm).\nconst slotCenters = [-12, -4, 4, 12];\nconst ventCutters = slotCenters.map((sx) =>\n  BREP.box([2, 5, 12]).translate([sx, 25 - 2 + 0.001, 9.75]),\n);\n\n// --- PCB mounting bosses (4 corner posts on the cavity floor) ---\n// 5 mm dia (r=2.5) × 5 mm tall, bored 2 mm dia (r=1) × 4 mm deep from the top.\n// Cavity inner footprint: x ∈ [-37, 37], y ∈ [-22, 22]. Inset 5 mm from each\n// inner wall → boss centres at x = ±32, y = ±17.\n// BREP.cylinder(r, h) has its base at z=0 — translate to put base on floor (z=3).\nconst bossCenters = [\n  [-32, -17], [32, -17], [-32, 17], [32, 17],\n];\nconst bossPosts = bossCenters.map(([bx, by]) =>\n  BREP.label(BREP.cylinder(2.5, 5).translate([bx, by, 3]), 'shell', { color: '#27ae60' }),\n);\n// Bore: top of boss at z=8; bore from z=4 to z=8.1 (4.1 mm deep).\nconst bossBores = bossCenters.map(([bx, by]) =>\n  BREP.cylinder(1, 4.1).translate([bx, by, 4]),\n);\n\n// --- Assemble ---\n// 1. Carve the cavity, the lid lip step, and the vent slots out of the shell.\nconst shelled = BREP.cutAll([outer, cavity, lidLip, ...ventCutters]);\n\n// 2. Fuse in the mounting posts (which rise from the cavity floor).\nconst withBosses = BREP.fuseAll([shelled, ...bossPosts]);\n\n// 3. Drill the screw bores down through each boss.\nreturn BREP.cutAll([withBosses, ...bossBores]);\n",
